Field.Name: Current
Field.Description: The currently used version of the software identified by the CurrentVersion Object.

Field.Name: Pending
Field.Description: The pending version of the software that could be installed identified by the PendingVersion Object.

Field.Name: Fallback
Field.Description: The fallback version of the software identified by the FallbackVersion Object.

Field.Name: KeepsParameters
Field.Description: If KeepsParameters is not set, the device will lose its configuration during update. The Client should do a backup of the parameters before the update and restore them afterwards.

Field.Name: WillDisconnect
Field.Description: If WillDisconnect is set, the OPC UA Server will restart during installation. This can be the case if the update is about the firmware of the device that hosts the OPC UA Server.

Field.Name: RequiresPowerCycle
Field.Description: If RequiresPowerCycle is set, the devices require a manual power off / power on for installation.

Field.Name: WillReboot
Field.Description: If WillReboot is set, the device will reboot during the update, inclusive of embedded infrastructure elements like an integrated switch. An update Client should take this into account since the devices behind an integrated switch are not reachable for that time.

Field.Name: NeedsPreparation
Field.Description: If NeedsPreparation is not set, the Client can install the update without maintaining the PrepareForUpdateStateMachine. This can be used to support an installation without stopping the software.

Relates the source node to a reference measurement instrument, like for example a calibration target using a reference measurement instrument.

UAVariableType.Description: Represents the specific quantity and value (with engineering unit) that a calibration target provides for calibration of equipment.
Represent a scale of calibration values. The value defines the range (lowest and highest value), and the resolution property the size of each step.

UAVariable.Description: Contains the audio data, e.g. for devices capable of audio playback.

UAObjectType.Description: Abstract base type for categorizing calibration targets. Subtypes define the concrete categories.

Characterizes a calibration target to be used together with a measurement instrument, that determines the values to be calibrated. It can be a piece created during the normal production process or an item specifically created for calibration purposes. The calibration target represents an individual piece or item, that is, if a new piece should be used or item is created, a new Object of this ObjectType is created.

Categorizes a calibration target to be used only once, for example because the calibration destroys the target. Typically, Objects of this ObjectType do not represent one individual calibration target, but a batch of calibration targets with the same characteristics.

Categorizes a calibration target to be reused several times. For example, a calibration target like a meter, that is bought specifically for calibration and not destroyed by an individual usage is of this category.
Categorizes a calibration target to be a reusable device that produces a certain environment like pressure that can be used for calibration.
Base interface for managing statistical data.

UAVariable.Description: Indicates the point in time at which the collection of the statistical data has been started.

UAObjectType.Description: Base interface for managing statistical data that is not rolled over all data from the start of tracking the statistical data are considered, until the tracking gets reset.

UAVariable.Description: The reason and context for the reset of the statistics, which is done without a trigger from an OPC UA Client, like calling the ResetStatistics Method. ResetCondition is a vendor-specific, human readable string. ResetCondition is non-localized and might contain an expression that can be parsed by certain clients. Examples are: “AFTER 4 HOURS”, “AFTER 1000 ITEMS”, “OPERATOR”. “OPERATOR” means, that an operator resets the statistics on a local HMI.

UAObjectType.Description: Base interface for managing statistical data that is rolled over, i.e. only a certain amount of data is considered for statistical data.

UAVariable.Description: The duration after the statistical data are rolled over. Only the data that were gathered during that duration are considered for the statistical data, even if the time intervals between the StartTime and the current time is longer.
The number of values before the data gets rolled over. For the statistical data, only the data fitting into the number of values is considered, even if more data were gathered since StartTime.

UAObjectType.Description: Provides information about a calibration target.

UAObject.Description: Defines what category the calibration target is of.
A folder containing information about the features of a calibration target, that is, what can be calibrated with the calibration target.

UAVariable.Description: A calibration value indicates the value the calibration target provides for calibration and includes its quantity and engineering unit.

A capacity range indicates a range (low and high value) as well as a resolution, and thus defines a number of values the calibration target provides for calibration and includes the quantity and engineering unit.
Contains the Uri of a certificate of the calibration target, in case the calibration target is certified and the information available. Otherwise, the Property should be omitted.

UAObject.Description: Provides identification information.

UAVariable.Description: Provides the date, the calibration target was validated the last time. If there is no specific validation date known, the date when the calibration target was bought or created should be used.

Provides the date, when the calibration target should be validated the next time. If this date is not known, the Property should be omitted. Note: Potentially the NextValidationDate is in the past, when the next validation did not take place.

UAObject.Description: A folder containing information about operational conditions of the calibration target. For example, it might provide in what ranges of humidity the calibration target can be operated. It might also provide correction information, for example, depending on the temperature the calibration values need to be corrected (in case of a length, the length might increase with high temperatures). If no operational conditions are provided, this folder should be omitted.

UAVariable.Description: Provides the quality of the calibration target in percentage, this is, the value shall be between 0 and 100. 100 means the highest quality, 0 the lowest. The semantic of the quality is application-specific.

Field.Name: Undefined
Field.Description: The EDM spark generator state cannot be indicated.

Field.Name: Ready
Field.Description: Generator is initialized and can receive a set of technology parameters.

Field.Name: Active_Low_Voltage
Field.Description: Generator is switched on and is supplying pulses respecting the low voltage (≤ 25 V AC or ≤ 60 V DC) requirements of safety standard (ISO 28881).

Field.Name: Active_High_Voltage
Field.Description: Generator is switched on and is supplying pulse at high voltage (> 25 V AC or > 60 V DC).

Field.Name: Error
Field.Description: Generator is in an error state.

Generator is in an error state.

Field.Name: Undefined
Field.Description: The laser state cannot be indicated, for example because the device does not provide this information or because it is currently unavailable. This can be e.g. during the startup phase.

Field.Name: Ready
Field.Description: The laser is ready and laser programs can be started. No error state is active. In this state, laser emission is prohibited.

Field.Name: Active
Field.Description: In this state, safety clearances have to be set for processing and emission can be activated. For devices that can run programs themselves it indicates that a program is running on the laser device.

Field.Name: Error
Field.Description: An error state is reported from the laser device.

uax:Description.uax:Text: The laser state cannot be indicated, for example because the device does not provide this information or because it is currently unavailable. This can be e.g. during the startup phase.
The laser is ready and laser programs can be started. No error state is active. In this state, laser emission is prohibited.
In this state, safety clearances have to be set for processing and emission can be activated. For devices that can run programs themselves it indicates that a program is running on the laser device.
An error state is reported from the laser device.

Field.Name: Manual
Field.Description: The machine is controlled manually, by the operator. Depending on technology specific norms, the maximum axis movement speeds of the machine tool are limited.

Field.Name: Automatic
Field.Description: Operating mode for the automatic, programmed and continuous operation of the machine. Manual loading and unloading workpieces are possible when the automatic program is stopped. Axis movement speeds are fully available to the machine tool’s ability.

Field.Name: Setup
Field.Description: Depending on technology specific norms, the maximum axis movement speeds of the machine tool are limited. In this mode, the operator can make settings for the subsequent work processes.

Field.Name: AutoWithManualIntervention
Field.Description: Operating mode with the possibility of manual interventions in the machining process as well as limited automatic operation started by the operator. Depending on technology specific norms, the maximum axis movement speeds of the machine tool are limited.

Field.Name: Service
Field.Description: Operating mode for service purposes. This mode shall not be used for manufacturing any parts. This mode shall only be used by authorized personnel.

Field.Name: Other
Field.Description: The machine operation mode is different from the values defined in this enumeration.

uax:Description.uax:Text: The machine is controlled manually, by the operator. Depending on technology specific norms, the maximum axis movement speeds of the machine tool are limited.

Operating mode with the possibility of manual interventions in the machining process as well as limited automatic operation started by the operator. Depending on technology specific norms, the maximum axis movement speeds of the machine tool are limited.
Operating mode for service purposes. This mode shall not be used for manufacturing any parts. This mode shall only be used by authorized personnel.
The machine operation mode is different from the values defined in this enumeration.

Field.Name: CapabilityUnavailable
Field.Description: The machine tool is not able to give a statement about the part quality.

Field.Name: Good
Field.Description: The part quality is determined good.

Field.Name: Bad
Field.Description: The part quality is determined bad.

Field.Name: NotYetMeasured
Field.Description: The PartQuality will still be determined in the machine tool to be either Good or Bad.

Field.Name: WillNotBeMeasured
Field.Description: The machine tool will not give a statement about the part quality.

uax:Description.uax:Text: The machine tool is not able to give a statement about the part quality.
The part quality is determined good.
The part quality is determined bad.
The PartQuality will still be determined in the machine tool to be either Good or Bad.

Field.Name: CapabilityUnavailable
Field.Description: The machine tool is not able to give a statement about process irregularities.

Field.Name: Detected
Field.Description: A process irregularity has been detected.

Field.Name: NotDetected
Field.Description: There was no process irregularity detected.

Field.Name: NotYetDetermined
Field.Description: A statement about the process irregularity is to be expected.

uax:Description.uax:Text: The machine tool is not able to give a statement about process irregularities.
A process irregularity has been detected.
There was no process irregularity detected.

Field.Name: Time
Field.Description: The tool life indicates the time the tool has been in use or can still be used. The value shall be given in hours (decimal value).

Field.Name: NumberOfParts
Field.Description: The tool life indicates the total number of parts that have been produced or can still be produced using the tool. The unit shall be „one“.

Field.Name: NumberOfUsages
Field.Description: The tool life indicates counting the process steps this tool has been used or can still be used (for example usages of a punching tool). The unit shall be „one“.

Field.Name: Feed_Distance
Field.Description: The tool life indicates the sum of the feed path covered by the tool and the workpiece relative to each other during machining. This value shall be given in one of the following units: millimetres, metres, kilometres.

Field.Name: Cutting_Distance
Field.Description: The tool life indicates the sum of the lengths that the cutting knife works in the workpiece. If the knife is not fixed, this includes the lengths of the arc segments of the knife path. This value shall be given in one of the following units: millimetres, metres, kilometres. uax:Description.uax:Text: The tool life indicates the time the tool has been in use or can still be used. The value shall be given in hours (decimal value).
The tool life indicates the total number of parts that have been produced or can still be produced using the tool. The unit shall be „one“.
The tool life indicates counting the process steps this tool has been used or can still be used (for example usages of a punching tool). The unit shall be „one“.

The tool life indicates the sum of the feed path covered by the tool and the workpiece relative to each other during machining. This value shall be given in one of the following units: millimetres, metres, kilometres.
